    <fr:title text="Monoid (algebra)">Monoid (algebra)</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>In algebra a <html:em>monoid</html:em> is a collection (a set) of elements equipped with a binary operation (multiplication) which has the properties of being associative and having a unit (identity) element. Formally, we say tht it is a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> equipped with the structure <fr:link href="/notes/002n/" title="Monoid (algebra)" uri="https://kaierikniermann.github.io/notes/002n/" display-uri="002n" type="local">(1)</fr:link>:</html:p>
    <html:ul><html:li>A <html:strong>binary operation</html:strong> (or <html:em>multiplication</html:em>) map from the cartesian product of the set with itself to itself, that is:
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    (-) \cdot  (-) : M \times  M \to  M
  ]]></fr:tex></html:li>
  <html:li>A <html:strong>neutral</html:strong> (or <html:em>identity</html:em>) <html:strong>element</html:strong> 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    1 \in  M
  ]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ul>
    <html:p>Such that the following properties hold:</html:p>
    <html:ul><html:li>The elements are <html:strong>associative</html:strong> w.r.t the operation, that is:
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \forall  x, y, z \in  M \vdash  (x \cdot  y) \cdot  z = x \cdot  (y \cdot  z)
  ]]></fr:tex></html:li>
  <html:li>Composition with the identity element is a <html:strong>unit</html:strong>, that is:
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \forall  x \in  M \vdash  1 \cdot  x = x = x \cdot  1
  ]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ul>
  </fr:mainmatter>
